document_data.History:
When [[Shar]] created the [[Shadowfell]], the Demiplane of Dread fragmented and each Darklord's realm settled into a spot somewhere within the newly created plane, possibly attracted by the plane's sinister nature. Within the Shadowfell, these realms became known as the '''Domains of Dread'''. Despite Shar's dominance of the Shadowfell, the Dark Powers still had control over each of these Domains.{{Fact}}

[[Castle Spulzeer]] in [[Tethyr]] was sucked into the demiplane by a magical gem set in the hilt of the dagger ''Aggarath''. [[Jander Sunstar]] suffered a similar fate after he swore revenge for his dead love, and the Lost King of [[Cormyr]], [[Gondegal]], has gained a position of power as the leader of the Knight of the Shadows order, a secret society dedicated to the protection of the helpless and oppressed.<ref> 

Several residents of [[Faer√ªn]] have even risen to the level of Darklord: [[Harkon Lukas]], the [[cormyr]]ian [[wolfwere]]; [[Hazlik]], a [[red wizard]]; [[Urik von Kharkov]], an escaped magical experiment; [[Draga Salt-Biter]], a [[Sword Coast]] pirate turned [[wereshark]]; [[Rengard Boltsmann]], a [[Harper]] that got infected with a strain of lycanthropy from Ravenloft;

Over the centuries, the accounts of Torilians who entered the Domains of Dread and made it back were written down. Many of these [[book]]s found their way into [[Candlekeep]]. By the 15{{th}} century [[DR]], the Domains of Dread became rarely discussed by the sages of Candlekeep as the topic of the [[Spellplague]] and [[Second Sundering]] overtook them in prominence.{{Cite archive/Greenwood's Grotto/2023-02-25/Candlekeep's lore on other worlds}}

Sometime in the late 15th century DR, reports of [[werewolf]] attacks and [[Vistani]] sightings in [[Daggerford]] and surrounding areas indicated that a passage into one of the Domains of Dread might have been present somewhere in the [[Misty Forest]].
